Saudi National Shipping to Sign Four Vessel Orders Tomorrow

-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 
2011-03-05T07:47:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-05/saudi-national-shipping-to-sign-four-vessel-orders-tomorrow-1-.html
National Shipping Co. of  Saudi
Arabia  will sign four shipbuilding contracts valued at 1.5
billion riyals ($411 billion) with  Hyundai Mipo Dockyard (010620) 
tomorrow.  National Shipping will seek 80 percent of the financing
from banks and the Public Investment Fund, the Riyadh-based
company said in a statement to the  Saudi bourse website . It
wants shariah compliant financing with tenors of 12 years, it
said.  National Shipping will begin receiving the cargo ships at
the end of 2012, the statement said. The value of the orders
includes building two additional optional ships, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
 mharoutunian@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Shaji Mathew at 
 shajimathew@bloomberg.net  